1 or t o immediately manage, direct, supervise, or control the sale or
2 service of alcoholic beverages; and
3 2. "Seller-server training certificate" means a certificate
4 granted for completing an Oklahoma seller-server certification
5 course recognized by the ABLE Commission.
6 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
7 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-130.1 of Title 37A, unless
8 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
9 A. Certain actions of an employee are not attributable to
10 an establishment licensed by the Alcoholic Beverage Laws Enforcement
11 (ABLE) Commission and shall be an affirmative defense to such
12 liability when such licensed establishment receives a notice of
13 violation for certain actions of an employee.
14 B. The following actions of an employee of a licensed
15 establishment are not attributable to the licensed establishment:
16 1. The selling, furnishing, or giving of an alcoholic beverage
17 to:
18 a. a person who is insane or mentally deficient,
19 b. a minor, or
20 c. an intoxicated person; or
21 2. Allowing the consumption of an alcoholic beverage by:
22 a. a person who is insane or mentally deficient,
23 b. a minor, or
24 c. an intoxicated person.
