1 C. A licensed establishment may assert the affirmative defense
2 if the license establishment:
3 1. Required all employees to maintain a currently valid
4 employee license from the ABLE Commission;
5 2. Required each employee to present a seller-server training
6 certificate within fourteen (14) days of his or her initial
7 employment date, unless the employee is deemed exempt by an existing
8 statute and require each employee to attend a seller-server training
9 course every two (2) years upon renewal of the employee license and
10 attend a seller-server training course every two (2) years after the
11 initial employment date, unless an employee is exempt pursuant to
12 Section 2-121 of Title 37A of the Oklahoma Statutes;
13 3. Adopted written policies and procedures which prohibit:
14 a. the sale, service, dispensation, or delivery of an
15 alcoholic beverage to:
16 (1) a person who is insane or mentally deficient,
17 (2) a minor, or
18 (3) an intoxicated person, or
19 b. the employee from allowing consumption of an alcoholic
20 beverage by:
21 (1) a person who is insane or mentally deficient,
22 (2) a minor, or
23 (3) an intoxicated person; and
